def: Composed of bone; resembling bone; capable of forming bone;bony; ossific.
Of or pertaining to crimination; tending to incriminate;criminatory.
One who shoots with a crossbow. See Arbalest.
A siliceous sponge, of the genus Hyalonema, and allied genera;-- so called from their glassy fibers or spicules; -- called alsovitreous sponge. See Glass-rope, and Euplectella.
One of the quinoline bases, obtained from coal tar as an oilyliquid, C11H11N; also, any one of several substances metameric with,and resembling, cryptidine proper.
A pungent kind of snuff made from the darker and ranker kindsof tobacco leaves.
The act or process of voiding excrement.
A bright-colored European actinian (Anemonia, or Anthea,sulcata); -- so called because it does not retract its tentacles.
A fringe, or fringed border.(b) A band of white matter bordering the hippocampus in the brain.-- Fim"bri*al, a.
